## Data provenance

The estimates were derived from de-identified CPRD primary-care data under
ISAC protocol [protocol number]. The published deposit contains ONLY
aggregated incidence rates and confidence intervals at the demographic-
stratum level; no individual-level data, identifiers, or low-count cells
violating disclosure-control rules are included.

## Disclosure control

Cells with fewer than 5 incident events have their numerator set to NaN
in the parquet. This follows CPRD's standard suppression rule. Users
re-aggregating across strata may legitimately recompute totals that
exceed the suppression threshold; this is acceptable practice and does
not constitute re-identification.
